Description: CVE-2026-4046 - Fix assertion failure in IBM1390/IBM1399 iconv converters
 The iconv() function may crash due to an assertion failure when converting
 inputs from the IBM1390 or IBM1399 character sets. When converting combined
 DBCS characters that expand to two Unicode code points, the converter
 previously required space for both code points upfront. If the output buffer
 only had room for one, the assertion on the combined character result would
 fail. This fix uses pending character state to buffer the second code point
 when the output buffer is too small, and flushes it on the next call or
 during state reset.
Origin: upstream, https://sourceware.org/git/?p=glibc.git;a=commit;h=d6f08d1cf027f4eb2ba289a6cc66853722d4badc
Bug: https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33980
Author: Florian Weimer <fweimer@redhat.com>
Last-Update: 2026-04-22

